BCE Inc.


            
            BCE, Inc. engages in the provision of communication services to consumer, residential, business, and government customers. It operates through the following segments: Bell Wireless, Bell Wireline, and Bell Media. The Bell Wireless segment provides integrated digital wireless voice and data communications products and services to residential and business customers. The Bell Wireline segment offers data, including Internet access and Internet protocol television, local telephone, long distance, as well as other communications services and products to residential, small and medium-sized business, and large enterprise customers. The Bell Media segment includes television, radio, out-of-home advertising, and digital media. The company was founded on February 25, 1970 and is headquartered in Verdun, Canada.

            
            (See Full Profile)


  




